379
00:32:40,751 --> 00:32:44,003
It's a second-class ticket
on the Ardlethen out of Rotterdam.

380
00:32:44,087 --> 00:32:48,633
I can't make out the holder's Christian name,
but his surname is Petrizzi.

381
00:32:48,717 --> 00:32:51,677
I looked it up
and the ship arrived here just last month,

382
00:32:51,762 --> 00:32:55,181
so there's a possibility
Mr. Petrizzi is still in town.

383
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:08,152
I found that
in the inside pocket of Mr. Speight's jacket

384
00:33:08,236 --> 00:33:10,488
after the coroner sent over his clothes.

385
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:16,577
The pages have been mostly washed clean,
but there is one entry there.

386
00:33:19,539 --> 00:33:21,290
Pasteurella pestis.

387
00:33:23,085 --> 00:33:25,169
Well, that's bubonic plague.

388
00:33:29,675 --> 00:33:31,676
Is that the brain of Mr. Carton,
your morphine addict?

389
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:34,428
No, no, no, no.
This is just a lab sample.

390
00:33:34,513 --> 00:33:37,056
Mr. Carton is still very much alive.

391
00:33:37,724 --> 00:33:40,101
So...

392
00:33:41,353 --> 00:33:44,855
