508
00:42:56,532 --> 00:43:00,494
is the story of America.

509
00:43:17,428 --> 00:43:21,682
Dr. Everett Gallinger,
may I present Dr. Samuel Reid.

510
00:43:22,558 --> 00:43:24,476
- Pleasure to meet you.
- How do you do?

511
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:27,354
We were just discussing
a most distressing problem

512
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:30,440
concerning mental defectives
in our community.

513
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:34,152
Your advice on the matter
would be invaluable, Everett.

514
00:43:34,237 --> 00:43:36,238
- Won't you have a seat?
- Thank you.

515
00:43:40,868 --> 00:43:45,747
Dr. Gallinger, I operate the idiot house
on Randall's Island.

516
00:43:45,832 --> 00:43:50,085
It's a state-financed home for boys
the courts have deemed to be morons.

517
00:43:50,169 --> 00:43:52,379
Sounds like a worthy institution.

518
00:43:52,463 --> 00:43:58,176
The problem is once the boys reach manhood,
we are legally bound to release them,

519
00:43:58,261 --> 00:44:04,349
which, unfortunately, leaves them free
to engender more idiots like themselves.

520
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,144
I see.

521
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:11,064
Well, gentlemen,
I believe I have a solution for you.

522
00:44:12,233 --> 00:44:16,903
So then he said to her,
"Well, I'm not Mark Twain."

523
00:44:36,257 --> 00:44:37,716
- All right, dear?
- Mmm.

524
00:44:39,052 --> 00:44:40,886
Maybe a little port.

525
00:44:46,267 --> 00:44:49,186
Forgive my appearance, Miss Everidge,

526
00:44:49,270 --> 00:44:51,271
but I didn't want to miss you.

527
00:44:52,273 --> 00:44:55,859
Bertie's given me clippings
of all your stories.

528
00:44:56,361 --> 00:44:57,652
Oh.

529
00:44:58,279 --> 00:45:00,364
And did you have a favorite?

530
00:45:01,699 --> 00:45:04,910
I think it's the one
where you dined with the Red Indians.

531
00:45:07,163 --> 00:45:09,623
I'm just glad
you came back with your scalp intact.

532
00:45:09,957 --> 00:45:11,291
Bertie.

533
00:45:11,959 --> 00:45:13,877
Didn't you read the clipping?

534
00:45:13,961 --> 00:45:16,463
They were very civilized hosts.

535
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:20,342
They would never scalp a guest,
especially such a lovely one.

536
00:45:22,220 --> 00:45:26,848
Bertie was telling us that Genevieve also
translated a paper for him from the Polish.

537
00:45:26,933 --> 00:45:30,644
Yes, Dr. Zinberg was duly impressed.

538
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:33,980
A linguist as well as an adventuress.

539
00:45:34,774 --> 00:45:36,817
How did you come to learn Polish?

540
00:45:36,901 --> 00:45:40,570
It's my parents' native tongue.
I spoke it growing up.

541
00:45:40,655 --> 00:45:42,364
Your parents are Polish?

542
00:45:42,448 --> 00:45:44,199
Mmm, Galician Jews.

543
00:45:44,909 --> 00:45:45,909
Oh.

544
00:45:47,703 --> 00:45:50,747
I hope that doesn't present a problem.

545
00:45:50,832 --> 00:45:53,875
After all, your savior was also a Jew.

546
00:45:53,960 --> 00:45:55,544
There's some debate about that.

547
00:45:56,087 --> 00:45:58,672
No, well, he was a Jew, all right.

548
00:45:58,756 --> 00:46:00,799
You know how you can tell?

549
00:46:00,883 --> 00:46:04,428
His mother thought he was a god
and he thought she was a virgin.

550
00:46:37,879 --> 00:46:40,672
I hope I wasn't being too presumptuous,

551
00:46:40,756 --> 00:46:43,175
but I saw you hiding your hands earlier.

552
00:46:44,135 --> 00:46:45,927
It's very kind of you.

553
00:46:47,096 --> 00:46:52,559
I'm afraid I haven't had the strength lately
to take proper care of myself.

554
00:46:53,978 --> 00:46:58,565
Well, I could come back next week
and varnish them, if you'd like.

555
00:46:58,649 --> 00:46:59,983
You mean paint them?

556
00:47:01,068 --> 00:47:02,319
Good heavens.

557
00:47:03,404 --> 00:47:06,656
I've never in all my life
painted my fingernails.

558
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:09,284
My mother would turn over in her grave.

559
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:16,333
You know, I don't think I've ever seen
quite such a large handbag.

560
00:47:18,794 --> 00:47:20,921
Well, tool of the trade.

561
00:47:21,005 --> 00:47:23,298
"Allzeit bereit," as the Germans say.

562
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:24,716
"Always prepared."

563
00:47:26,052 --> 00:47:27,636
Would you like to see?

564
00:47:28,763 --> 00:47:30,472
If you don't mind.

565
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:36,770
Well, my reporter's notepad
and pencil, of course.

566
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:41,191
Press credentials.

567
00:47:42,652 --> 00:47:43,652
Um...

568
00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:45,779
My billfold.

569
00:47:49,075 --> 00:47:52,536
A lucky kachina doll,
given to me by the Hopi.

570
00:47:54,038 --> 00:47:56,790
This is a photograph of my parents.

571
00:48:01,003 --> 00:48:03,255
And a photograph of Bertie.

572
00:48:12,974 --> 00:48:16,184
I don't know how my family's going to get on

573
00:48:20,147 --> 00:48:21,314
when...

574
00:48:24,777 --> 00:48:26,152
With help.

575
00:49:00,730 --> 00:49:04,024
Well, thank you
for the best meal I've ever eaten.

576
00:49:04,692 --> 00:49:07,569
Well, the first of many, I hope.

577
00:49:13,909 --> 00:49:15,535
Whiplash.

578
00:49:16,203 --> 00:49:19,372
An injury caused by a sudden strain
to the muscles of the neck.

579
00:49:43,189 --> 00:49:45,231
Who died, Mr. Barrow?

580
00:49:46,359 --> 00:49:47,901
What do you mean?

581
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:52,739
My father told me
riches and honors depend upon heaven.

582
00:49:52,907 --> 00:49:53,907
Ah.

583
00:49:54,909 --> 00:49:58,536
Well, I hardly knew my father.

584
00:49:59,747 --> 00:50:01,915
Consider yourself fortunate.

585
00:50:01,999 --> 00:50:04,417
Mine was a violent man and a son of a bitch.

586
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:07,671
Did he come here
to work on the railroad?

587
00:50:09,632 --> 00:50:11,841
The California Gold Rush.

588
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:20,725
He insisted I be educated
in accordance to strict Confucian principles

589
00:50:21,185 --> 00:50:24,062
in expectation of the day
he would strike it rich

590
00:50:24,146 --> 00:50:26,314
and we would return to China.

591
00:50:31,278 --> 00:50:35,490
He wouldn't even permit me to learn English
when I was still young enough to master it.

592
00:50:40,621 --> 00:50:44,708
But he never struck the mother lode
and I fell in with gangsters.

593
00:50:46,043 --> 00:50:48,962
I suppose I was
a great disappointment to him.

594
00:50:56,804 --> 00:51:00,140
Your debt to me
is now repaid in full, Mr. Barrow,

595
00:51:00,224 --> 00:51:03,184
and this part of our business
has come to an end.

596
00:51:04,895 --> 00:51:06,312
Not quite.

597
00:51:07,815 --> 00:51:12,485
I'd like to discuss a remedy
to Junia's indentured state.

598
00:51:13,821 --> 00:51:15,405
A remedy?

599
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:20,285
Do I understand you to mean
I am some kind of disease?

600
00:51:21,287 --> 00:51:24,247
Forgive me. I spoke thoughtlessly.

601
00:51:25,166 --> 00:51:27,625
You spoke like a man who runs a hospital.

602
00:51:28,627 --> 00:51:29,836
$3,000.

603
00:51:33,174 --> 00:51:34,758
$1,500.

604
00:51:34,842 --> 00:51:36,009
$2,000.

605
00:51:36,677 --> 00:51:37,719
Done.

606
00:51:38,387 --> 00:51:39,596
Very good.

607
00:51:47,396 --> 00:51:48,480
Oh.

608
00:51:49,023 --> 00:51:51,232
I'll have the money for you shortly.

609
00:51:54,612 --> 00:51:59,699
Then rest assured I will keep her safe
and gainfully employed until you do.

610
00:52:56,090 --> 00:52:58,550
Gentlemen,

611
00:52:58,634 --> 00:53:01,094
the source of addiction.

612
00:53:14,441 --> 00:53:16,860
The place is perfect
for a man such as yourself.

613
00:53:16,944 --> 00:53:18,778
A family man of means.

614
00:53:19,238 --> 00:53:22,198
That's how you would describe yourself,
isn't it, Mr. Barrow?

615
00:53:22,283 --> 00:53:23,700
Beg your pardon?

616
00:53:23,784 --> 00:53:27,036
- I believe you said you have two children.
- That's right.

617
00:53:27,121 --> 00:53:29,414
The nursery is on the ground floor

618
00:53:29,498 --> 00:53:31,666
and this is the parlor,

619
00:53:31,750 --> 00:53:35,712
a gracious stage for your wife
to entertain upon.

620
00:53:35,796 --> 00:53:39,591
My wife will never see
the inside of this room, I assure you.

621
00:53:39,675 --> 00:53:41,009
I'm sorry?

622
00:53:42,261 --> 00:53:44,637
Nor even my kiddies.

623
00:53:44,722 --> 00:53:45,722
How much?

624
00:53:45,806 --> 00:53:48,308
$7,000 for two floors facing the street.

625
00:53:48,392 --> 00:53:51,728
The ones facing the park are somewhat more.

626
00:53:51,812 --> 00:53:53,730
A steal, I assure you.

627
00:53:53,814 --> 00:53:58,067
Once the subway opens,
your investment will soar.

628
00:54:02,323 --> 00:54:03,823
Mr. Carton?

629
00:54:06,994 --> 00:54:09,203
Mr. Carton, can you hear me?

630
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:35,021
Let's get started.

631
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:41,611
Will you come with me, Moishe?

632
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:53,373
Do what the nice man tells you to do.

633
00:54:55,793 --> 00:54:58,962
Your name is Moishe? You're a Yid?

634
00:54:59,046 --> 00:55:00,797
Uh, yes, sir.

635
00:55:00,881 --> 00:55:02,048
Very good.

636
00:55:02,132 --> 00:55:04,717
Remove your trousers
and hop up on the table.

